This paper proposes a new training method for feedforward neural networks, which falls under the category of neural networks and machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on the activation functions with the geometric contraction property, which is a common topic in the subfield of neural networks (cs.NE). The experiments conducted in the paper involve classification tasks, which are also relevant to the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the experiments involve image classification, which is a common application of neural networks in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the functional construction of the neural network, which is relevant to the subfield of signal processing (cs.SI).
